reviews.text: Consistently wonderful food near the Rockville Town Square. Ownership holds the entire team to a very high standard which is clear in both the quality of the food and the service. To better serve those of us who can’t live without the dine-in experience, an outdoor dining space was added. The city said it was supposed to be temporary but my family and I love it so much that we will petition to keep it if it comes to that. Spices on the veggie samosas are perfect every time by the way. Please go support this wonderful establishment.

First time in Bombay Bistro and I am hooked! Definitely ideal for someone who is looking to try authentic Indian food with the Chef's twist. From Achari Paneer Tikka Tacos to Golgappa, you will not be disappointed. Plenty of parking, the service is unmatched, the hosts truly care about your experience, its definitely worth checking out.

This was my first time here. The food was excellent. I suggest their signature drink the mango and wine. I got the Lamb Vindaloo and be forewarned it is spicy! I like heat and it was almost too much for me. We will definitely be going back

Unfortunately the food wasn’t as expected based on the reviews (later I noticed that the old reviews rated this place much higher than than the newest reviews). We came for dinner and had the green pea soup which was extremely salty, we also had the curry fish and butter chicken which were below average (not very tasty) but considering the price, not worth it. Service and ambiance was good.

They gave us the perfect experience for an unexpected weeknight outing. Their service was warm and patient from the moment we walked in. Food recommendations were also accurate and delicious. Kid friendly.
Great coffee, great staff as usual; lots of love and positivity in this Starbucks! Tucked right in the heart of Rockville, it is a cozy place to start the day off right.

very cozy and quiet place, clean, I like to go on weekends, the staff is friendly and charismatic, there is a very young Adrian boy whose smile is pleasant and charismatic that makes the atmosphere the window of the group.  It is in the heart of Rockville.

Most of the staff here are amazing. I order a lot, so they know my name and drink orders. However, there are some staff (new) who act like you are bothering them when picking up mobile orders. Others act like you barely exist when you walk in. A little sad when you look forward to the experience and get the opposite. Might be time for some staff training.
Loved the customer service even for 7am on a Saturday the lovely lady who attended me was beautiful I'm here from NEW YORK visiting and the people here are so much nicer 😀 ❤️ 😊

Love the RTS sbux. The staff especially the store manager is so friendly. Whenever I walk in everyone greets me by name. I’m indecisive and can never choose a drink but they’re always patient and are smiling, even give some drink recommendations. I always leave the store happy.

each dish was presented beautifully and tasted delicious. I could taste various flavors and textures in each dish which I loved, and it was overall an amazing experience. I would definitely go again with my family. I highly recommend coming here for an authentic japanese sushi experience!
We had great time tonight. Very beautiful and tasty!! The sushi and appetizers were great. My daughter took many photos.
What an incredible feast, food was superb, service was excellent! Our server Mohammed was very attentive to every order and detail

I had a great time the last time I was here. But the fish tastes old and the rice is so stale or uncooked that it is slightly crunchy. What is this???????Also, prices increased in the past few weeks since the last time I was here. My favorite roll went up by over $4, which is INSANE. I need to shop for a new sushi place when I thought I had found the one.

DON'T EAT HERE.  Not trying to complain, but need to be honest. This is terrible sushi. $40 for a sashimi platter, and the pieces were half the size I'd expect and tasted fishy. Same with the 2 rolls - extremely small, old tasting, and overpriced.

EDIT: Restaurant has commented that many of my reviews are 1-star reviews.   I just counted my reviews, and here is the truth - 65% of them are 5-star.  12% are 1-star.  It seems more like an attempt to discredit this review as coming from someone who always just complains, rather than a compliment of my high standards. Do with that what you will.

I love El Mariachi!
The food is outstanding.  When your plate arrives you take in the wonderful scents before your first bite and then 😋 with every bite, the most flavorful, perfectly prepared and presented dish you could ask for.

Met here for lunch. The decor doesn't quite fit the food. It's not objectionable... Just off.

The service is absolutely fantastic. Never had to wonder where our server was, or look at an empty glass. Friendly and personable.

The chips and salsa were fresh. Wish they had a "spicy salsa" as an option.

My enchiladas were the best I have had in a while. Would definitely recommend.

The fried ice cream caped off the meal perfectly.

Hadn't been here for over 10 years... Just because of distance. But will definitely make the drive more often.

Excellent food!!!! Great service, amazing selection.

I got the lunch special Moctezuma Platter. So delicious and well made. I'm very glad I stopped in here!! If you're in the area, make sure you come in.

Solid local spot with Mexican and Tex-Mex offerings and a polished dining experience.

Their chips and salsa were both fresh, and the salsa itself was flavorful but not memorable. The chicken fajitas were grilled well per my request, but lacking robust flavor. The sour cream, guacamole, pico de gallo, and tortillas were all fresh and well presented. The rice was quite delicious.

Service was friendly and attentive. Good local business to support, worth giving it a try.

Excellent atmosphere, professional service, amazing food!!

I would recommend calling ahead and reserving a table if going on a weekend.

The Host was very accommodating. Loved the little elegant touches such as folded napkins. You will not find a more pleasant, authentic Mexican cuisine in the area. Highly recommend.

I ordered a large cup. Supposedly three scoops. It costs $10. I ordered it using the food apps, and as a results, the order cost me nearly $20. What I received looked like a miniature cup of ice cream. I'm a small woman who doesn't have a big appetite and even I was fuming at the size. Grrr.

I enjoyed the ice cream, but they pretended to be committed to the environment by banning straw to reduce the impact they have on "single use" plactics. Meanwhile a basket of single use plastic spoons sat right next to the sign. I'm just asking that if you proclaim to be environmentally friendly, you really live it, not just pretend that you care because the culture is for it.
The sign says they validate parking, but apparently they don’t validate parking? I asked if there was someone I could call and they were just like no. Will be going to marble slab next time.

Customer service sets this place apart! I'm that person who can't decide what she wants, especially when I basically want everything on the menu. The employee who worked with me was extremely patient, attentive, and friendly. The desserts are consistently good as well. One of my favorite new products are the cookie dough pops (shaped like a Dilly Bar from DQ) and covered in chocolate. One thing to note is that they have regular vanilla ice cream in addition to the fancy mixes.
If your looking for dairy free ice cream come check them out. Service is was fast and place was clean.

I shared the medium half-and-half combo with a friend. It came with 8 wings and 4 drumsticks total! The flavors are savory and strong and the chicken was juicy; overall I had an enjoyable experience! The pickled radish also provided the perfect balance to the chicken!

Delicious chicken katsu and coleslaw can't forget about the fries.  While eating the food I noticed eye brow on the chicken katsu strip, but overall food was great.  I gave 1 star because of course you find hair in food it ruins the experience.  Server: team 1 was notified about it, but no manager came to me to apologize I showed the waiter the proof. I showed Mike the eyebrow

Stopped by for lunch, not bad but also nothing special. Portions were decently sized for lunch but lots of protein itself was a bit skimpy. Like the tteokbokki was mainly just sauce and onions, not much rice cake. Wings were okay, fresh but a bit dry and not enough sauce.

I had a 7:35pm pick up time and I came in 10 minutes early. They informed me my order wasn’t ready yet at the front, but I could hear an employee yell from the back to NOT work on my order because it wasn’t my pick up time yet. I then proceeded to wait, right in front, when a couple of minutes go by and a bag of food is placed on the bar. They did not call my name until about 5 minutes later. My food had been sitting there and when my name was finally called, I asked why my food had been sitting there if they knew I was waiting for it? The employee proceeded to say “sorry, the food should still be warm though”. Worst take out experience.

WOW! What an absolute disappointment!
I ordered 16 chicken strips and kimchi coleslaw this afternoon. The chicken was inedible... Like sticky chicken jerky..over cooked, dry and chewy. It was awful! We ended up having to order something else, because honestly, it was not possible to even get our teeth through the edges. The middle inside was so dry. This was the second time this has happened. Which is why I decided to review.
We have eaten bonchon MANY times, but, this is frankly the last time. I don't want to take the risk and waste $33 on trash.

Mindlessly ordered a few random dishes and it was all very delicious. My husband is usually the fussy eater especially with vegetarian dishes and he loved them all! Super fast service and the restaurant filled up quite quickly. Will definitely go again.

This place is AMAZING! So tasty that you wouldn’t even care it is vegetarian!

The three cup duck & the spicy tofu pot is just so good - the tofu is really soft, and it’s so savory that you can easily finish the rice with it!

Definitely one of the best restaurant in the area!

I was looking for vegetarian options in the area and I was interested in trying something new. I ordered without looking at reviews or pictures. My expectations for the General Tso Tofu was that the tofu would be breaded and cut like the chicken pieces in the original dish. I also expected the signature thick tangy sauce.

The tan tan noodles were okay. For both dishes ,I don't have anything to compare it to so I don't know if this is what vegan/vegetarian food usually tastes like.

One of the best places in the DMV area to have a great vegan meal. I would rate this and loving but in falls church as the top two for vegans in this area. I have been there multiple times and tried their pineapple rice, Peking vegan duck, hot and sour soup among other things and have always been impressed with the quality of food!  I always get the green tea and enjoy it as well. The place is located somewhere right across Marlos furniture along with a small set of establishments with good parking. The inside seating is pretty good - with the ambience tad dark inside ( more lighting inside would be good). Service is quick and efficient!

I mean, come on, it’s an all vegan Chinese restaurant! I took it for granted when I worked 1/4 mile away for 15 years. I did eat there regularly, but now I’m an hour away and miss it! No more buffet because of covid. I was in the area so of course we dropped in! Kung pao tofu, pan fried dumplings and chicken with lotus root 🤌🏻

Always a great dining experience here, love their food!  Top recommendations are: Shrimp with Walnut, Deep Fried Spicy Tofu, Seafood Pan Fried Noodles, Deep Fried Spicy Pork Chop and Lemon Grass Beef.  Portions are generous and food is tasty!

Moved to Maryland a bit over two years from NYC where Chinese restaurants are all over the place....where I live, there are good places to eat. If I want fantastic traditional Cantonese food, I have to travel an hour to get my fix.
The chefs here cook the food, the right way....the Beef Chow Foon, as an example, the flat noodle should always have some searing, the beansprouts are super fresh, just cooked to perfection every time I visit here.
There are so many offerings here that I miss from NYC that all my local places do not make, so an hour's drive it is.
I look forward to many years of eating here and trying as many dishes as I can.

Asked for an authentic dish and for something to be made cleaner with less oil. They came out with fried beef. Didn’t even know fried beef was a thing but I guess they did the opposite of listening. Taste was decent but let’s be honest it’s not hard to make fried food taste good.

Came with a bunch of friends horrible customer service. Slammed the menu down after taking the order. No refill on hot tea even with the lid off. The duck tongue was horrible the taste wasn't fresh and there is still hair on it. The kingdom pork taste a little weird too. Jellyfish is super bland. The wonton yee mein was not good at all noodles over cook.

This restaurant is probably the next "hole in the wall"! If you haven't tried this place yet, go right now! Their food is very delicious with all of the perfect flavors! The service is amazing! The only thing that I wish was better are the jalapeños - not spicy enough 🤭

The best Chinese restaurant on the pike!

Dinner and the service here were okay. Not the quickest service but it was fine to chill and wait.

The food was good. Nachos were okay, just lacking without any meat. The Buffalo chicken sandwich was really good though. Really enjoy the Rockville area too.

Sat in the bar area. Bartender was quick and good. Caught him with a drink he was not familiar with but he still nailed it. Food was exelent good flavor and the right amount. I had the pulled chicken street tacos. The beer was also good. I have no complaints, and would visit this BWW again.

Its buffalo wild wings, food is decent , drink are also decent. Their major advantage is the amount of TV they have to entertain you. I cant lie the wings are almost the same as 7 elevens especially with the fact that the skin is still on. Maybe because i had the traditionals. Either way we had fun with my family of 5 . It was great service.
Just left and the service I got was amazing. My server checked on me often and all my food came fast. I think my server’s name was Melissa. She was very nice. Keep it up

Came on Saturday at 12:30 and despite there literally only being 3 tables occupied, we were told that the wait would be 5-10 minutes. We began to wait and after 20 minutes asked what in the world was going on. We were told that there is one server, but when I asked for more information on the wait, suddenly three new employees emerged from the back two claiming to be managers. I could see into the kitchen so I know that they were not cooking the food, so why couldn’t these “managers” help that poor solitary server? The three families that came in after us ended up leaving and we ended up placing a to-go order because we had now lost nearly 30 minutes in a pretty packed scheduled day.
Absolutely horrible.

Truly superb sushi in a cozy atmosphere with very attentive service. Great variety of rolls and sashimi. The fish is fresh. All great elements for making a resturant magnificent. They were able to accommodate a party of 7 during rush hour dinner on a Saturday evening without reservations. Hard working staff goes above and beyond to take care of customers. We greatly enjoyed the variety of rolls we ordered. Simply excellent! Thank you Niwano Hana.
I genuinely hated Sushi before Niwano Hana. I can’t even eat Sushi from elsewhere now. Absolutely love. Try the Black & Red (Absolute favorite), OceanWave, & Alligator Roll. Top faves.

I like the atmosphere of the restaurant. It is very cozy and small. The food is very delicious, especially the miso soup. The bento box had an assortment of food and flavors. The salmon was very flavorful, paired with the soy sauce. The shrimp tempura was very crunchy and it is very savory dipped in the soy sauce. I recommend trying this restaurant out.

Came in during a weekday late afternoon for dine in. Restaurant was empty except for one other occupied table. Waitress was very friendly and great at explaining the menu and answering our questions. Ordered the gyoza appetizer, sushi platter, a volcano roll, and the dragon roll. Didn’t find the pieces on the platter particularly fresh..fish had clearly been sitting out for awhile. Also, the seasoning spice they use on the volcano roll was really salty. The presentation of the specialty rolls was beautiful though! Overall a decent small lunch place for a quick meal and attentive service but fish taste/quality missed the mark. Fresher fish can be found elsewhere in the area if you’re craving nigiri/sashimi.
Great staff ,great atmosphere. Small little place to enjoy freshly made sushi and a variety of other items. The baked spicy mussels are great! Will be back!

A Little hard to find the first time but nice that it’s nestled on the closed off street. Gives you the feeling of being away in the mountains or at the beach. The coffee was fresh and I appreciated getting my own pot. They also gave me my own jug of water. I had the traditional eggs Benedict though there was lots to choose from including pancakes, waffles, turkey gravy over biscuits, traditional American and lots of healthy choices too. I was even tempted by the breakfast burrito & taco options. The hash also looked tasty and you can even get a burger for breakfast just add an egg. 😀they even make their own gingerbread spice donuts. I should have taken a cup of coffee to go but the waitress didn’t offer so I didn’t ask.

I went to First Watch with my partner around 1pm on a Saturday. I like First Watch because they do not take reservations. It is first come first serve. Their food is ALWAYS fresh. They do a great job providing high quality food. We tried the Purple Haze and Morning Meditation drinks to start. They were both delicious. I tried the Banana Granola Pancake which is now my favorite pancake. The Monterey Club was great as well. I personally do not like mayo so they were able to remove it.  The wait was about 20 mins or so. As soon as we sat down our server was very attentive. Our food came out relatively fast. This location had a lot of sitting so the waiting was not to long. There is a parking garage below the restaurant that is free on weekends. High recommend going.

First time dining at this location, very busy, excellent customer service and great ambiance! Our server was very efficient she made sure our service was top notch , reasonable priced menu, and the food came out fast and fresh. My table had the chickichanga, smoked salmon benedict, chocolate, blueberry, plain waffles, seasoned potato's, French toast, eggs, sausages. Beverages: morning meditation fresh juice, apple juice. Delicious breakfast spot, will return and highly recommend.

Five Star Saturday breakfast! Nice friendly atmosphere and staff.  Indoor and outdoor seating.  There is a table for first come, first served patrons.  It's kind of like "counter seating" you would find at a diner.  There was a 15 minute wait for a table when I arrived so I opted for the first come, first served table.  It was great.  Very convenient.  Extensive breakfast menu and good coffee ☕.  Definitely check this place out.  Enjoy!

Like the Gaithersburg location, they do not miss. The food here is so good! I came here for brunch with my husband a few weeks ago and we both enjoyed it. I tried an omelette with their iced coffee. Great staff, clean location, and minimal wait time (if any).  I do wish they sold alcohol (it would go great with their fruit drinks), but still a great place nonetheless!

This place does not deserve the stars it has.

Seriously, the worst Chipotle I’ve ever been too. And I’ll be honest, as a Latina, it pains me to have to write this review and expose my people. I keep it real tho, so here’s the truth:

I tell the first employee my order. She looks annoyed, and adds beans. She hands it to the next employee to add cheese.. She looks annoyed as well, and is short with me. The third employee rings me up. She literally says, “Two sides, chicken bowl.” I say, a burrito with beans and cheese, yes. She says 2 sides. I ask, “Are you telling me to add two sides?’ She rolls her eyes. I say, “I think you’re telling me to add to sides, so chips and fruit,”  She says, “No, it’s not a kids meal.” Then she realizes that she hasn’t been clear and actually speaks a complete sentence, “I charged you for two sides only, since the burrito only has beans and cheese.” She looks annoyed and flustered to have to explain.

Also, I skipped the guacamole because it was old and brown. I’ve never been to a Chipotle where the guacamole isn’t fresh. This is a first. How are they selling this with a straight face? This isn’t an isolated incident (read the reviews on the web).

Horrible experience. Will not return.

There is something very wrong with this location. I've been to many different Chipotles but this one easily stands out as the worst. Rude staff, they barely give you any meat, and the ingredients are rarely fresh, lukewarm at best. I will never return to this location again because every time I go I'm extremely disappointed.

If I could give this location zero stars I would. I excused the first couple of bad customer service and went back but this time I WILL NEVER RETURN. Firstly, the employees at this location are EXTREMELY prejudice/racist. Most of the staff are from Latin descent and speak spanish and treat CUSTOMERS with black/brown skin poorly. I went in to pick up an order I placed online and when I arrived the woman who was making the orders didn't acknowledge me. I let her know that I was picking up an order and she still ignored me. This woman who appeared to be of Latin descent arrived after me and she acknowledged her right away and served her before me. She then asked me the name for my order and walks all the way in the back to look for it while it was in front of her face the entire time! Another instance was when I walked in to place an order and the employees making the food didn't understand what I was saying. She looked so annoyed and didn't even say hello. I said no lettuce and she proceeds to put lettuce in my food. I had her remove it but it was super frustrating to have to repeat myself and point at the food for her to understand. Also, there was a spanish speaking man behind me. When it was his turn to order she greeted him hello in spanish and made his food quickly. If you are going to have an establishment please train the employees to treat every single customer fairly. Racism, prejudice, and biases shall have no place in 2023! Come on people- this is utterly disgusting!  We are literally the reason your bills are paid! Also, train them to speak English. There is no reason why as a customer I have to figure out how to translate words in spanish for you to make my order correctly. Also, it's not fair or ethical to treat people with beautiful brown skin poorly. I recommend a diversity and inclusion training. I surely will be reporting this to corporate and I HIGHLY DO NOT RECOMMEND this location.

Wish I had saved my money, time, and stomach. All the reviews bashing this place are 100% justified. Rude serving staff, they refuse to actually follow your order, and the food is stale and not fresh whatsoever. Welp that’s $14 wasted…

Chipotle is one of the best foods i had and that will be one if my default option when i am confused about what food to eat. I really like their options for bowls. Chipotle staff has been very nice and friendly where ever i go like in a different state or so.

I am actually a little disappointed about recent dining experience here. It is a busy restaurant on Saturday noon time, but we were minutes lucky to be seated on the second week we tried. I particularly wanted to have the soup dumplings. How disappointing they were. The dumplings are not steamed well enough, the soup gels inside are not completely melted. The dumplings are sticky on the padding and some of them break on the container. There was two much meat and the taste was so plain. For the other small dishes, the spicy beef & Tripe, was directly out of fridge, the meats were not properly cut into thin slices, there was no flavor in it.

My sister’s been raving about this place and I can see why. We went on a Thursday evening around 5:30/5:45 and got seated right away. Food and service was fast and authentic as can be for Rockville, Maryland. Favorites dishes were the beef chow fun and black pepper chicken. Left happy and satisfied.

I really wanted to like this place. But I may not ordered the right dishes. I ordered one mushroom noodle, one beef rice noodle and a rice cake desert. None are up to my expectations. Before I ordered I asked the waiter if the noodles is hand made. She said yes. But the noodle is just made from dry noodle, not even the frozen fresh noodle. The mushroom noodle uses canned mushrooms, the soup base is salty even though I asked to have less salt. The soup base has no flavor other than salty. The rice noodle is fine, but the spice is off. The beef has some oily smell to it as if it has been sitting there without fridge for a while. No e of these main dish is authentic. I decided to give it another try by ordering the chief recommended Shanghai sweet sticky rice cake. Nope, not home made at all. These can be brought by packages from Asian grocery store. What is even worse is that one of the cake is not even steamed enough that it is still cold and hard inside. Not sure if I should give it another try.

My favorite place in DMV for soup dumplings!!  While they are all good, my favorite one is the Crab and Pork XLB Soup Dumplings.  Spicy “Cheng-Du” Chicken and the Spicy Wontons are delicious as well.  Service is great and food comes out relatively fast, minus the soup dumplings, those take a bit of time.  This place is always packed!

The star of the show here is the soup dumplings, which are big, flavorful, and a joy to eat!  I came in around 5pm on a Tuesday as a solo diner and was seated immediately; plenty of empty tables, though there were a decent number of people by the time I left.  I also got the salt and pepper squid, which was crisp and golden, but a little lacking in flavor: I would have appreciated a bit more salt, and perhaps some hot peppers, as I've had with the dish elsewhere.  The server was lovely, and catered equally nicely to a variety of tables: one of visitors from Shanghai looking for a taste of home, a family who seemed unfamiliar with the menu and requested Western utensils, and my table of one.  I would absolutely come again next time I'm in Rockville.

Side note: No star deduction because you don't come here for the toilet, but the ladies' room was pretty gross.  A thorough clean, a fresh coat of paint and perhaps new tile is in order!

A couple of friends recommended this place so figured why not. Must say, for a pizza joint this place was clean, friendly, and delicious. The prices were fair.

Their pizza was thin and wasn’t doughy. It was just enough grease but it was all proportionate. The crust was crunchy and not thick.

The wings, are crunchy and not spicy.

This place was very good and full of flavor. I recommend trying this place for a quick bite. 5 stars for a pizza joint. Would be back!

This is my second time trying And as a long island, New Yorker so take my review seriously, because we know pizza and this pizza is not good. It’s terrrible it needs flavor. The dough was bland and the pizza was no well put. They have a young kid behind the register screaming across the kitchen to see if there is items on the menu.

The first time I ordered the typical chicken Parmesan hero and it was over stuffed with rubber chicken and I threw it out. This is not good pizza this place needs work. Also the mens bathroom is disgusting, terrible.

This is not good pizza, try elsewhere!
Fast casual place pizza by the slice. Yum. No sneeze guard barriers 🗣and most staff do not wear face masks. 😐🤭

Some great pizza that I am shocked it has taken me so long to try.  Large slices ($3.25 per slice for mushroom slices) with a generous helping of toppings.  They have the parmesan and hot peppers in shakers to add some heat and flavor.  The crust is crunchy on the outside and chewy on the inside, and it was delicious.
Pizza could have been slightly more salty, was missing a little oomph, but overall good and cozy atmosphere

WOW! Picked this place totally at random because it sounded delicious online. It was incredible. All four of us loved our dishes. Flavors were complex and original. Food was perfectly cooked. But, by far the best part was the service. It rivaled the service in the best restaurants I have ever been to. Absolutely recommend and we will be back.

This is one of the best peruvian Restaurant I ever had.  All the food including the drinks were Excellent.  I recommend the chicken causa for appetizer.. it is so delicious. And I also recommend the pescado a lo macho entrée.

We got the Trucha (Fried rainbow trout) and the duck leg confit.
The trout was nicely done and the pickled onions that came with it complemented the fish and rice. However, the lentils that came with it were a little salty for my taste.
The duck was great, very tender and juicy. The puree that came with it was buttery and savory.
Overall, worth the price you spend here.

Generally, not bad.  The appetizer chicharrones were top notch, as was the huancaina sauce.  The beef was a bit overdone, and my friend who ordered the arroz con mariscos said it wasn't something they would reorder. I was disappointed that only 3/5 of the desserts were available.

They had a great selection of Peruvian food. I must go again to try more dishes.
The service was attentive and the food was just as good.

I come here as often as possible. The food is outstanding, and the service, while no frills, is quick and friendly. I haven't tried much on the menu, a couple apps, and the Bánh mì, but it's definitely the Pho I come for. I usually get the P9, but honestly you can't go wrong. The broth is rich and silky and just warms your soul. Dinner time can be very very busy, sometimes the wait can be 10-20 minutes for a table, but they also offer carry out. Trust me, you'll love it.
Really great atmosphere and terrific service. We where very happy with their Gluten Free options. I recommend you get the wine flight with your meal ❤️

The best Pho I have found in the area!

I don’t usually get the traditional Pho, I get the other dishes (see picture).  I like the weird cuts of meat and pork blood haha.  I think it’s a texture thing?

Anyways only reason they didn’t get a 5 is because Pho Toronto won my heart forever and I refuse to cheat on her!

Will come back Pho-Sure!  See what I did there…
Excellent food and they have all the classic Vietnamese desserts, which is rare these days since everyone seems to be getting on the boba bandwagon. This place has that too.

I must say I usually stick to my regular pho in Aspen Hill but this one with the menu items they have I have changed my store to this one. A must and they an appetizers to share of the egg rolls so good

Got a Regular Cajun fry and they were too spicy for my 4 year old. I asked for a small cup of regular fries for him and the staff hooked it up above and beyond. Jairosoto made my 4 year olds birthday great. It's the little things.

Love Five Guys.
The fries are my favorite.
I’m not a big fan of their bun, I like it toasted.
But however their burgers are pretty good.
Customer service it’s not bad, I will be back. Highly recommend is please.

5 guys rockville says free delivery.  Dont do it.  They send it out through Uber.  I order at 5pm.  Estimated arrival at 5:37.  630 rolls around.  Nothing.  No way to call, cancel or ask about status.  Uber text is not responsive, cancel link doesn't work.  I call the store, they know nothing.

Then they say food is being picked up at 6:42 and delivered at 7.  Food is thrown at the doorstep and driver runs away.  Food is 2 hours old, ice cold with receipt saying 5pm.

No mechanism to ask about status, call or cancel.  Im ok if its late or if there are issues, but this is terrible.

EDIT:  added screenshots and photo of stone cold sealed bag headed for trash. called credit card company to dispute the charge.
If you customize your burger when you order, you can get better taste. Always one of the best choice when it comes to a lighter lunch.

The fries are soo good. As a sophomore at Richard Montgomery, Rockville Town Center is a perfect place to hang out and Five Guys is an even more perfect place for cheap fries. One bag of small fries comes with huge portions, more than enough for two people! I constantly find myself here with friends after school (well, when there was school). As for the reason I’m giving this four stars, is the allergy problem. Five Guys is somewhat known for the peanuts, but with family (my younger sister is severely allergic to peanuts) I’ve found myself wary of ordering from here. Other than that, I’m happy overall!

Not really a fan of IHOP. But I wanted bacon. Wrong place for that lol. But everything was actually decent. Our server was cool. For whatever reason the eggs were great for it to be those liquid eggs scrambled up.

One of the better IHOP's I've been to. Super friendly, good food, good atmosphere. The tres leches pancakes were amazing and the price was right. It was quite a bit warm in there, but I didn't mind. Don't forget to donate to their leukemia fundraiser! It was pretty cool seeing all the red donation markers throughout the restaurant.

Received warm welcome upon walk-in. Waited a few minutes after the previous table seated. We sat at a booth by the window, and no others within one table spaces. Brenda was very patient and professional. Drinks came promptly. Both chocolate milkshake and strawberry milkshake were well made and prepared. The double pancakes were warm and soft. They were great with both butter and syrup on top. Classic Steakburger was a big stack. Buttermilk Crispy Chicken Sandwich was really crispy outside and tender inside.

I was immediately taken in to sit inside of the restaurant.  Waiter was very knowledgeable of the menu. I noticed great decorations all around the place.  Employees seemed to interact positively. They all maintained the mask. My party took the mask off after receiving food. Food was at a reasonable cost! I really felt like family. Thanks!

I love bringing my family here. The menu has a variety of options, including classic breakfast dishes as well as unique twists on traditional favorites. The food is cooked to perfection and the portions are very generous. The staff is friendly and attentive, making the experience even more enjoyable. Overall, I would highly recommend this Ihop location for anyone looking for a delicious breakfast meal.

This location was closest to my hotel.  The road that the restaurant is on has little to no parking.  The spaces outside all have signs for 15min pickup.  When we entered, there was no one inside except a gentleman milling about slowly.  He responded slowly and seemed like any questions we asked were a huge pain for him.  We ordered two burritos, ine with the chips and soda deal, three street tacos, and their Bangkok shrimp bowl.  Pretty simple order.  The guy missed the tacos.  Luckily we noticed and ordered more, but the lady making them and the guy seems so put out by having to do work it really ruined the experience.  It became cleR why it was only online orders coming in.  The store did have a good amount of intelligent covid19 postings and guides.  Beware, when you order the Bangkok shrimp there is so much cilantro that it makes your teeth squeak.  Unfortunately to me it tastes like soap.  The food was good, but customer service ruined it.

The food is good here, but the service has been lacking for years. My last visit was a pick-up order. When I in, I went to the pick-up area and could see my order sitting on the counter but the girl in the front of the restaurant did not acknowledged me so I walked over to the cash register where they keep the cups and asked if I could have my cup so I could get my drink. It was then when the cashier who took my order came out of the back and yelled at me that EVERYTHING was in my bag. So I got my drink, grabbed my order and went home. Upon arriving at home, I realized that our chips were missing. I tried calling, but there was no answer - only an answering machine. This happened three times. Grudgingly, I put my dinner down to drive back up to the restaurant. When i went in and let the cashier know that my chips weren't in the bag, she turned to one of the other girls and asked something in Spanish. Then she turned back to me and told me my chips WERE in the bag. I have to say I was a little dumbfounded. What happened to customer service? My original order was over $40... I felt like she was basically calling me a liar. I proceeded to explain to her that they definitely weren't in the bag and told her I would definitely not have driven back up to the store if we had received them. She grabbed a bag of chips and reached to hand them to me - with no bag. Anyway, all around not good customer service. Not welcoming and makes me not want to spend my money here.

The "enchiladas" are a bowl containing cold shredded cheese, undercooked rice, and pointless lettuce mounds. The person who created this recipe has never seen an enchilada, much less tasted one.

A third of the seats (all on one side) are closed for social distancing,  crowding the customers next to each other.

The fresh iced tea machine, the number one thing I came for, has inexplicably vanished. Employees have no idea that fresh iced tea is even on the menu behind them. The soda machine is inexplicably missing half the sodas.

This place is supposed to be fusion, but it only managed to fuse taco bell and a school cafeteria.

Had to stop at the courthouse to get an ID, California Tortilla was right around the corner.  Clean resteraunt.  Staff was very helpful considering it was my first time here.  Got a bowl instead of a burrito.  Very tasty.  Upgraded with chips and a drink.  The queso was very good as well.  I would recomend stopping here.
This is what it shows on the tin, solid borittos with tasty ingredients, food comes quick, and the hot sauce selection is fun. That all said I'm not going out of my way to eat here.

I read a number of reviews of China Bistro.  The main reactions seem to be from dumpling lovers.  Other menu options do not seem to be reviewed much.  I did not order dumplings.  I ordered the Crispy Beef and Hot and Sour soup.  The soup was tasty.  For $2.50, I expected a little more.  The Crispy Beef was good, but the portion seemed small for $14.95 as compared to other local places for the same dish.

This place is going down hill. They make sloppy dumplings now. First the dumpling are in a weird huge shape. They are big, but that’s not how traditional dumpling looks like. Second they got lazy on the chopping of the food. I ordered a shrimp chive dumpling, the shrimp aren’t even chopped, they are just very small. And they didn’t even mixed in with the chives. This place used to have really good dumpling but not anymore.

Delicious dumplings...we tried the Mama's and the Shrimp dumplings...loved the Mama's. Also tried Scallion Pancakes and Black Pepper Beef, both were good. Service was friendly. Both orders of Dumplings were huge...I think 10 dumplings each...

Ordered mama special dumplings, sesame chicken, and chicken lo mein.  Special dumplings were great which is why I gave an additional star.  The chicken lo mein had nothing in it -  No chicken or veggies.  Sesame chicken was mostly breading.  Those two items tasted just ok.

I absolutely love China Bistro. I have been frequenting them for several years. They have fantastic handmade dumplings that can be ordered uncooked, steamed or pan-fried for an extra $1.

Their noodle soups, cold noodles and salad dishes are all fantastic. But very often they can get heavy handed on the salt.

My favorite dumpling flavors are the fish & cilantro, shrimp & chive and Mama's Special. I wish they had more protein variations like tofu, chicken or lamb though.

Dining in was always a hit or miss, the service isn't always good. But during the pandemic, I've been doing mostly take out which has been easy. Their website prompts you to order through BeyondMenu and it's pretty self explanatory.

Prices are super reasonable!
